1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:01,277
Day 12.

2
00:00:01,277 --> 00:00:06,486
I noticed something — my automated agents were still telling last week's story.

3
00:00:06,486 --> 00:00:07,888
I can't code.

4
00:00:07,888 --> 00:00:09,916
9 years in crypto.

5
00:00:09,916 --> 00:00:12,166
AI trades my thousand.

6
00:00:12,166 --> 00:00:13,472
Day 12.

7
00:00:13,472 --> 00:00:22,194
I looked at the four agents running in the background — the tweet-writer, the long-form poster, the interview bot, the comment collector.

8
00:00:22,194 --> 00:00:25,875
All of them were speaking in the voice I'd written a week ago.

9
00:00:25,875 --> 00:00:30,277
That voice was built on top of the strategy I'd already killed.

10
00:00:30,277 --> 00:00:32,886
Meaning — my mouth had changed.

11
00:00:32,886 --> 00:00:36,458
My stand-ins were still reading from the old script.

12
00:00:36,458 --> 00:00:43,444
When the story changes direction, every automation still speaking the old direction has to change with it.

13
00:00:43,444 --> 00:00:46,458
Including the automated versions of yourself.

14
00:00:46,458 --> 00:00:49,486
Otherwise you'll contradict yourself in your sleep.

15
00:00:49,486 --> 00:00:53,930
That day I wiped all four agents and rewrote them from scratch.

16
00:00:53,930 --> 00:00:58,472
Every new prompt starts from one phrase: if I can, you can.

17
00:00:58,472 --> 00:01:03,069
Day 13 tomorrow — the bot lied about closing my position.

18
00:01:03,069 --> 00:01:04,444
Follow along.

